    "instructions": [
        "In a large skillet over medium heat, add the ground beef seasoned with a pinch of black pepper. Cook, breaking up the meat with a spatula, until it is browned and cooked through, about 5 minutes.",
        "Add the butter, sliced bell peppers, chopped garlic, sliced shallots, and pickled (or fresh) ginger to the skillet. Cook together for 2 minutes to soften the vegetables and develop flavor.",
        "Pour in the tamari or soy sauce, then add the Gochujang, ginger juice, and 1/3 cup of water. Stir well and cook until the sauce thickens and coats the beef and vegetables, about 2-3 minutes.",
        "Stir in the maple syrup or honey and continue to cook, stirring regularly, for another 1-2 minutes until the beef mixture becomes caramelized. Remove from heat and toss with toasted sesame seeds.",
        "In a bowl, combine the chopped cucumbers with salt, optional chili flakes, Gochujang, ginger juice or rice vinegar, and chopped green onions. Let sit for 5 minutes to marinate.",
        "Spoon the beef and pepper mixture over cooked rice. Serve alongside the cucumber salad and top with chopped roasted peanuts."
